<title>USA: HBO &amp; Co sees charge for AMISYS.</title>
<headline>HBO &amp; Co sees charge for AMISYS.</headline>
<dateline>ATLANTA 1997-06-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>HBO &amp; Co said Friday it will take one-time charge for expenses related to its acquisition of AMISYS Managed Care Systems Inc.</p>
<p>The charge will be about $10 million and will be taken in the second quarter, said Beth Dalton of the company's investor relations department.</p>
<p>The company said it completed the acqusition, in which shareholders in the healthcare information systems provider received .35 of a share of HBOC common stock for each AMISYS share.</p>
<p>HBOC said at closing, about 2.7 million of its shares were issued for the roughly 7.8 million outstanding AMISYS shares. HBOC said the transaction will be accounted for as a pooling of interests.</p>
